======================================================================
KEY ANSWERS
======================================================================

Q: Does joint quantization recover meaningful sparsity?
A: On actual V1 weights (expert = ternary*scale, shared = FP16):
   Independent (A): 89.54% sparsity
   Joint global (B): 95.69% sparsity
   Per-row joint (C): 91.21% sparsity
   YES — joint quantization improves sparsity by up to +6.15%

   NOTE: V1 experts are clones. This result reflects quantization
   alignment only. Real gains require diverse trained experts (V3).
   Synthetic tests with noise_std=0.02 show the method's potential
   for properly trained experts.
